cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of learning a loss function for machine learning models, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. The paper presents an algorithm that is efficient and effective in learning loss functions, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category as it directly deals with the problem of learning loss functions. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it is a sub-category that encompasses machine learning and optimization. cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also relevant as they deal with applications of machine learning in image and natural language processing, respectively. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as it deals with optimization and learning in neural networks.
